#### [NEW] [state/scraper_state.py](file:///c:/Users/sksiv/Workspace/ai-agents/x-bookmarks-scraper/state/scraper_state.py)
- Supports split state: `incremental_state.json` and `historical_state.json`
- Stores resume checkpoints, last processed tweet ID, and runtime tracking.

---

### Entry Point

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///c:/Users/sksiv/Workspace/ai-agents/x-bookmarks-scraper/main.py)
- Orchestrate: init browser → check session → login if needed → navigate → scroll → extract → save
- Two modes: `incremental` (latest only) vs `historical` (full deep scan)
- Checkpoint resume logic: fast-scrolls to the last saved tweet in historical mode and continues
- Rate Limits & Human delays: 2-6s per tweet, 1-3s between scroll blocks.
- Time limit protection (`MAX_RUNTIME_MINUTES`)
- On completion of `historical`, passes newest tweet ID to `incremental` state for seamless future runs.

